   The Cuneiform tablets, especially those found at Elba state
   that Assyrian kings went across the desert and fought a battle at
   the great Egyptian river. Then they proceeded westward to fight
   another battle at the Nile. This implies that the great Egyptian
   river is between the Sinai and the Nile.
